"use strict";(self.webpackChunkarchlan_docs=self.webpackChunkarchlan_docs||[]).push([[2620],{4003:function(t){t.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"03-post-lightdm-iso","metadata":{"permalink":"/documentation/blog/03-post-lightdm-iso","editUrl":"https://github.com/archlan/documentation/edit/main/blog/01-09-post-lightdm-iso.md","source":"@site/blog/01-09-post-lightdm-iso.md","title":"Lightdm doesn\'t start on the live ISO","description":"When booting in the ArchLan live environment, it is possible that the lightdm display manager didn\'t start automatically. If it\'s your case, just run this command:","date":"2022-01-09T22:17:08.400Z","formattedDate":"January 9, 2022","tags":[{"label":"systemd","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/systemd"},{"label":"howto","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/howto"},{"label":"services","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/services"},{"label":"iso","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/iso"}],"readingTime":0.25,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Lanhild","title":"Developer/Maintainer of ArchLan Linux","url":"https://github.com/Lanhild","imageURL":"https://github.com/Lanhild.png","key":"Lanhild"}],"nextItem":{"title":"Start systemd services that weren\'t automatically enabled","permalink":"/documentation/blog/02-post-systemd"}},"content":"When booting in the ArchLan live environment, it is possible that the lightdm display manager didn\'t start automatically. If it\'s your case, just run this command:\\n```bash\\n# The password for the liveuser is \\"archlan\\"\\n$ sudo systemctl start lightdm.service\\n```\\n\\n>This issue will be fixed in the next releases."},{"id":"02-post-systemd","metadata":{"permalink":"/documentation/blog/02-post-systemd","editUrl":"https://github.com/archlan/documentation/edit/main/blog/01-05-post-archlan-systemd.md","source":"@site/blog/01-05-post-archlan-systemd.md","title":"Start systemd services that weren\'t automatically enabled","description":"During the ArchLan ISO building, the file runbeforesquashfs.sh executes operations in the last steps of the ISO building process.","date":"2022-01-05T22:00:27.437Z","formattedDate":"January 5, 2022","tags":[{"label":"systemd","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/systemd"},{"label":"howto","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/howto"},{"label":"services","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/services"}],"readingTime":0.55,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Lanhild","title":"Developer/Maintainer of ArchLan Linux","url":"https://github.com/Lanhild","imageURL":"https://github.com/Lanhild.png","key":"Lanhild"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Lightdm doesn\'t start on the live ISO","permalink":"/documentation/blog/03-post-lightdm-iso"},"nextItem":{"title":"Fix an issue with ArchLan packages repository signing","permalink":"/documentation/blog/01-post-packages"}},"content":"During the ArchLan ISO building, the file `run_before_squashfs.sh` executes operations in the last steps of the ISO building process.\\nSome of these operations might not succesfully work. If you encounter issues, follow the steps in this post to solve them.\\n\\n```bash\\n$ nmcli\\nError: NetworkManager is not running.\\n```\\nFollow the steps in this post to fix it.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n1. In order to get the NetworkManager service unit to work\\n```bash\\n$ sudo systemctl start NetworkManager.service\\n```\\nYou should now be able to use network connection on your machine.\\n\\n:::note\\nIn the case you are facing any other problems related to the ArchLan ISO, submit an issue at [ArchLan:Issues](https://github.com/archlan/iso/issues/new)\\n:::"},{"id":"01-post-packages","metadata":{"permalink":"/documentation/blog/01-post-packages","editUrl":"https://github.com/archlan/documentation/edit/main/blog/12-27-post-archlan-packages.md","source":"@site/blog/12-27-post-archlan-packages.md","title":"Fix an issue with ArchLan packages repository signing","description":"ArchLan Linux has it\'s own package repository added to the pacman configuration.","date":"2021-12-22T21:40:41.388Z","formattedDate":"December 22, 2021","tags":[{"label":"pacman","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/pacman"},{"label":"howto","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/howto"},{"label":"gpg","permalink":"/documentation/blog/tags/gpg"}],"readingTime":0.725,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Lanhild","title":"Developer/Maintainer of ArchLan Linux","url":"https://github.com/Lanhild","imageURL":"https://github.com/Lanhild.png","key":"Lanhild"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Start systemd services that weren\'t automatically enabled","permalink":"/documentation/blog/02-post-systemd"}},"content":"ArchLan Linux has it\'s own package repository added to the pacman configuration.\\nIf, at some point, you encounter this error while trying to update;\\n\\n```bash\\nerror: archlan-packages: signature from \\"Lanhild (ArchLan Linux PGP key, made by @Lanhild.) <archlan@protonmail.com>\\" is unknown trust\\nerror: failed to synchronize all databases (invalid or corrupted database (PGP signature))\\n```\\nFollow the steps in this post to fix it.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n1. The first step is to import the ArchLan Linux gpg key from the keyserver to your machine:\\n\\n```bash\\n$ sudo pacman-key --recv-keys 5F765E0E531F5B53\\n```\\n2. By precaution, verify the fingerprint of the key:\\n\\n```bash\\n$ sudo pacman-key --finger 5F765E0E531F5B53\\n```\\n3. The last step is to locally sign the key:\\n\\n```bash\\n$ sudo pacman-key --lsign-key 5F765E0E531F5B53\\n```\\n\\n:::note\\nOnce all these steps have been accomplished, you should be able to successfully update and install packages from the ArchLan repository.\\n:::"}]}')}}]);